    "slug": "tango",
    "path": "tango/overview.md",
    "content": "# Tango Chile Sauce â€” Brain\n\n## Current Understanding\n\nTango is a premium hot sauce brand with 6 flavors: Sriracha, Mango, Truffle, Mild, Thai, Hot. Revenue comes through multiple channels â€” Amazon (direct), UNFI (distribution to Whole Foods, etc.), EXP Corp, and emerging channels (Costco, DTC, Faire, Mable).\n\nThe business is real and generating ~$6,900/mo but the goal is $50K/mo by Q2 2026. The gap is $43,100/mo.\n\nProduction happens at Foodies (co-packing) with ingredients from Deep. Packaging from Acorn (boxes) and labels. Shipping via Daylight.\n\n## Goal\n\n**This month:** Ship EXP pallet, fix Amazon PPC, close DTC sales\n**12 months:** $30,000/mo across Amazon + UNFI + Costco + DTC\n\n## Key Learnings\n\n- Traffic is the bottleneck on Amazon, not conversion\n- PPC barely running (~$66 over 60 days) â€” massive untapped lever\n- Truffle = 63% of Amazon revenue\n- Mango mystery SOLVED: 14.7% conversion is market-rate\n- UNFI SoPac (LA) is WHERE THE GROWTH IS: +516% YoY\n- UNFI Northeast needs SKU expansion (no Mango)\n- Mango adds ~7 units/week net at Whole Foods\n\n## COGS & Margins\n\n| Flavor | COGS | UNFI Margin | Best Channel |\n|--------|------|-------------|--------------|\n| Sriracha | $2.74 | â€” | EXP 34%, Amazon 63% |\n| Mango | $3.31 | 31% | Best UNFI margin |\n| Truffle | $3.34 | â€” | EXP 60%, Amazon 70% |\n| Mild | $3.37 | 30% | Amazon 55% |\n| Thai | $3.42 | â€” | Amazon 54% |\n| Hot | $3.49 | 28% | Amazon 53% |\n\n## Production Costs (Per Run)\n\n| Item | Cost |\n|------|------|\n| Deep (ingredients) | $1,300 |\n| Foodies (co-pack) | $1,100 |\n| Boxes (Acorn) | $804 |\n| Labels | $1,500 |\n| Shipping (Daylight) | $400 |\n| **Total per run** | **$5,104** |\n\n## Channel Revenue Targets\n\n| Channel | Target | Current | Gap |\n|---------|--------|---------|-----|\n| Amazon | $10,000 | $3,500 | $6,500 |\n| UNFI | $10,000 | $3,400 | $6,600 |\n| Costco | $5,000 | $0 | $5,000 |\n| DTC | â€” | $0 | â€” |\n\n## Orders System (NEXT BUILD)\n\n**Goal:** Full order lifecycle management on Tango Dashboard\n\n### What We Need\n1. **Supabase `orders` table** â€” id, channel, po_number, value, date, stage (new/processing/shipped/paid), doc paths (po_url, bol_url, inv_url), notes, created_at, updated_at\n2. **Migrate dashboard from localStorage â†’ Supabase** â€” same pipeline UI, persistent data\n3. **Drop zone for new POs** â€” drag a PDF onto a box on the dashboard, it:\n   - Scans/parses the document for PO number, channel, value\n   - Creates a folder in `/Projects/ğŸ”¥ tango/orders-invoices/{channel}/{po-number}/`\n   - Moves the file into that folder\n   - Creates a new order card in the \"New\" column\n4. **Document export links** â€” PO, BOL, Invoice buttons on each card link to the actual files\n5. **Existing folder:** `/Projects/ğŸ”¥ tango/orders-invoices/` already has channel subfolders (Amazon, Costco, DTC, EXP, Faire, Mable, UNFI)\n\n### Architecture Decision\n- Order DATA â†’ Supabase (stage, value, dates, doc URLs)\n- Order FILES â†’ Local folders (PDFs stay on machine, organized by channel/PO)\n- Tango Dashboard reads from Supabase, displays pipeline, handles drag-and-drop\n- Drop zone intake: browser-side file handling â†’ parse â†’ create folder â†’ insert row\n\n## Files\n\n*Scanned Feb 16, 2026 from /Projects/ğŸ”¥ tango/ (symlinked at /âš¡ claudio/tango/)*\n\n| Folder | Files | What's In There |\n|--------|-------|-----------------|\n| amazon/ | 1,776 | Listings, A+ content, flat files, FNSKU labels, PPC data, screenshots |\n| brand/ | 2,834 | Labels, logos, nutrition facts, UPCs, 2026 brand system, rebrand assets |\n| business/ | 421 | Legal, FDA, insurance, certificates, BOL, food safety, CA compliance |\n| production/ | 1,201 | Kitchen photos, packaging suppliers, purchase orders, billing, label proofs |\n| distribution/ | 563 | UNFI docs, Costco materials, Faire, old retailers |\n| images/ | 2,882 | Product photography (new label, old label) |\n| sales/ | 264 | Decks, data exports, one-sheets |\n| marketing/ | 804 | Ads, collabs, events |\n| media/ | 1,086 | Video, audio, press, Pixar intro, No More Clog |\n| website/ | 1,847 | Old web builds, 2026-02-12 website data |\n| tangofest/ | 1,586 | The big summer event |\n| backburner products/ | 273 | Dragon Jelly, Gobblins, Mega Jerk |\n| orders-invoices/ | 23 | By channel: Amazon, Costco, DTC, EXP, Faire, Mable, UNFI |\n| merch/ | 55 | Hats, shirts, stickers, Tango Flame beanie |\n| social/ | 18 | Social media content (dated post folders) |\n| misc/ | 119 | Claude docs, inspiration, misc |\n| current bills/ | 3 | Active invoices/screenshots |\n| tango dashboard/ | 2 | Dashboard icon assets |\n",
